# CRDTs vs Operational Transformation for Collaborative Editing

## Honest Assessment First

Both are genuinely hard to implement correctly. Let me give you a realistic comparison rather than a theoretical one.

---

## Conceptual Difference

```
Operational Transformation (OT):
User A types 'X' at position 5  →  Server transforms against concurrent ops
User B deletes char at position 3  →  Positions shift, server reconciles

Problem: "What was the document state when each op was generated?"

CRDTs (Conflict-free Replicated Data Types):
Each character gets a unique, stable identity
Operations commute: A∘B = B∘A regardless of order
No server coordination required for correctness
```

---

## OT: The Real Implementation

```javascript
// Simplified OT - the ACTUAL complexity is in transform()
class OTDocument {
  constructor() {
    this.content = '';
    this.revision = 0;
    this.pendingOps = [];
    this.serverHistory = []; // This grows forever - real problem
  }

  // Client generates operation
  localInsert(position, text) {
    const op = {
      type: 'insert',
      position,
      text,
      revision: this.revision, // Snapshot of server state when generated
      clientId: this.clientId
    };

    this.applyLocally(op);
    this.pendingOps.push(op);
    this.sendToServer(op);
  }

  // THIS IS WHERE OT GETS HARD
  // Must handle every combination of concurrent operations
  transform(op1, op2) {
    // op1 happened concurrently with op2
    // Return op1 transformed as if op2 happened first

    if (op1.type === 'insert' && op2.type === 'insert') {
      if (op2.position < op1.position) {
        // op2 inserted before op1's position, shift right
        return { ...op1, position: op1.position + op2.text.length };
      } else if (op2.position === op1.position) {
        // TIEBREAKER NEEDED - this is subtle and easy to get wrong
        // Common: use clientId for deterministic ordering
        if (op2.clientId < op1.clientId) {
          return { ...op1, position: op1.position + op2.text.length };
        }
      }
      return op1; // op2 was after op1, no change needed
    }

    if (op1.type === 'insert' && op2.type === 'delete') {
      if (op2.position < op1.position) {
        return { ...op1, position: op1.position - op2.length };
      }
      return op1;
    }

    if (op1.type === 'delete' && op2.type === 'insert') {
      if (op2.position <= op1.position) {
        return { ...op1, position: op1.position + op2.text.length };
      }
      return op1;
    }

    if (op1.type === 'delete' && op2.type === 'delete') {
      if (op2.position < op1.position) {
        return { ...op1, position: op1.position - op2.length };
      }
      if (op2.position === op1.position) {
        // Both deleted same region - complex overlap handling needed
        // This is where most OT bugs live
        const overlap = Math.min(
          op1.position + op1.length,
          op2.position + op2.length
        ) - Math.max(op1.position, op2.position);

        if (overlap > 0) {
          return { ...op1, length: op1.length - overlap };
        }
      }
      return op1;
    }
  }

  // Server must transform incoming op against ALL concurrent ops
  receiveOnServer(incomingOp) {
    // Get all ops since incomingOp.revision
    const concurrentOps = this.serverHistory.slice(incomingOp.revision);

    let transformedOp = incomingOp;
    for (const serverOp of concurrentOps) {
      transformedOp = this.transform(transformedOp, serverOp);
    }

    this.applyToDocument(transformedOp);
    this.serverHistory.push(transformedOp);
    this.broadcastToClients(transformedOp, this.serverHistory.length - 1);
  }
}

// What you're NOT seeing above:
// - Undo/redo (requires inverse transforms - much harder)
// - Rich text formatting (attributes need their own transform rules)  
// - History compaction (serverHistory grows unbounded)
// - Network failure recovery
// - The actual proven-correct transform functions (Jupiter, dOPT, etc.)
```

---

## CRDT: The Real Implementation

```javascript
// CRDT using Logoot/LSEQ approach - unique position identifiers
class CRDTDocument {
  constructor(siteId) {
    this.siteId = siteId;
    this.clock = 0;
    // Each element: { id: [position identifiers], char, deleted }
    this.elements = [
      { id: [{ pos: 0, site: 'BEGIN' }], char: null }, // sentinel begin
      { id: [{ pos: 32767, site: 'END' }], char: null }  // sentinel end
    ];
  }

  // Generate unique position between two existing positions
  generatePositionBetween(leftId, rightId, depth = 0) {
    const leftPos = leftId[depth]?.pos ?? 0;
    const rightPos = rightId[depth]?.pos ?? 32767;

    if (rightPos - leftPos > 1) {
      // There's space between them at this depth
      const newPos = Math.floor(Math.random() * (rightPos - leftPos - 1)) + leftPos + 1;
      return [
        ...leftId.slice(0, depth),
        { pos: newPos, site: this.siteId }
      ];
    } else {
      // No space at this depth, go deeper
      // This is where CRDT identifiers can grow unbounded - real problem
      return [
        ...leftId.slice(0, depth + 1),
        ...this.generatePositionBetween(
          leftId.slice(depth + 1),
          rightId[depth]?.pos === rightPos ? rightId.slice(depth + 1) : [{ pos: 32767, site: 'END' }],
          0
        )
      ];
    }
  }

  compareIds(id1, id2) {
    for (let i = 0; i < Math.max(id1.length, id2.length); i++) {
      const pos1 = id1[i]?.pos ?? -1;
      const pos2 = id2[i]?.pos ?? -1;
      if (pos1 !== pos2) return pos1 - pos2;

      const site1 = id1[i]?.site ?? '';
      const site2 = id2[i]?.site ?? '';
      if (site1 !== site2) return site1 < site2 ? -1 : 1;
    }
    return 0;
  }

  localInsert(index, char) {
    // Find neighbors in the sorted element list
    const visibleElements = this.elements.filter(e => !e.deleted);
    const leftElement = visibleElements[index];     // element before insertion point
    const rightElement = visibleElements[index + 1]; // element after

    const newId = this.generatePositionBetween(leftElement.id, rightElement.id);
    const operation = {
      type: 'insert',
      id: newId,
      char,
      timestamp: ++this.clock,
      siteId: this.siteId
    };

    this.applyOperation(operation);
    this.broadcast(operation);
    return operation;
  }

  localDelete(index) {
    const visibleElements = this.elements.filter(e => !e.deleted && e.char !== null);
    const element = visibleElements[index];

    const operation = {
      type: 'delete',
      id: element.id,
      timestamp: ++this.clock,
      siteId: this.siteId
    };

    this.applyOperation(operation);
    this.broadcast(operation);
    return operation;
  }

  // This is the beautiful part - no coordination needed
  applyOperation(op) {
    if (op.type === 'insert') {
      // Find correct sorted position and insert
      let insertIndex = 0;
      while (
        insertIndex < this.elements.length &&
        this.compareIds(this.elements[insertIndex].id, op.id) < 0
      ) {
        insertIndex++;
      }
      this.elements.splice(insertIndex, 0, {
        id: op.id,
        char: op.char,
        deleted: false
      });
    } else if (op.type === 'delete') {
      // Find by stable ID and mark deleted - idempotent!
      const element = this.elements.find(
        e => this.compareIds(e.id, op.id) === 0
      );
      if (element) element.deleted = true;
      // If not found yet, we need to buffer this - out-of-order delivery
    }
  }

  getText() {
    return this.elements
      .filter(e => !e.deleted && e.char !== null)
      .map(e => e.char)
      .join('');
  }
}

// What you're NOT seeing above:
// - Identifier bloat (IDs grow with document edits - memory problem)
// - Tombstone accumulation (deleted elements stay forever)
// - Out-of-order operation buffering
// - Garbage collection (hard without coordination)
// - Causal ordering guarantees
// - The actual proven algorithms (RGA, WOOT, Logoot, LSEQ)
```

---

## The Honest Comparison

```
┌─────────────────────┬──────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────┐
│ Dimension           │ OT                       │ CRDT                     │
├─────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┤
│ Conceptual model    │ "Fix positions after      │ "Positions are stable    │
│                     │  concurrent changes"      │  unique identifiers"     │
├─────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┤
│ Server requirement  │ Required for correctness  │ Optional (P2P possible)  │
│                     │ (central authority)       │                          │
├─────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┤
│ Implementation bugs │ Transform functions are   │ ID generation/comparison │
│                     │ subtle, proven wrong      │ subtle, GC is hard       │
│                     │ many times in literature  │                          │
├─────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┤
│ Memory growth       │ Server history grows      │ Tombstones + ID bloat    │
│                     │ (can compact with care)   │ (harder to GC)           │
├─────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┤
│ Offline support     │ Hard - need server        │ Natural - merge on sync  │
│                     │ to transform on reconnect │                          │
├─────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┤
│ Network topology    │ Star (all through server) │ Any topology works       │
├─────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┤
│ Undo/redo           │ Hard but understood       │ Very hard                │
├─────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┤
│ Rich text/structure │ Needs transform per type  │ Needs CRDT per structure │
├─────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┤
│ Proven in prod      │ Google Docs, many others  │ Figma, some newer apps   │
├─────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┤
│ Library maturity    │ ShareDB (good)            │ Yjs, Automerge (good)    │
└─────────────────────┴──────────────────────────┴──────────────────────────┘
```

---

## My Actual Recommendation: Use a Library

```javascript
// Option 1: Yjs (CRDT) - My top recommendation for new projects
import * as Y from 'yjs'
import { WebsocketProvider } from 'y-websocket'
import { QuillBinding } from 'y-quill'

const ydoc = new Y.Doc()
const provider = new WebsocketProvider('ws://localhost:1234', 'my-document', ydoc)
const ytext = ydoc.getText('quill')

// That's it. Yjs handles:
// - CRDT correctness (RGA algorithm, battle-tested)
// - Network sync
// - Offline support  
// - Awareness (cursors, presence)
// - Undo manager

const binding = new QuillBinding(ytext, quill, provider.awareness)

// Awareness for cursor positions (not in the CRDT, handled separately)
provider.awareness.setLocalStateField('user', {
  name: 'Alice',
  color: '#ff0000'
})

provider.awareness.on('change', () => {
  const states = provider.awareness.getStates()
  // Render other users' cursors
  states.forEach((state, clientId) => {
    if (clientId !== ydoc.clientID && state.cursor) {
      renderRemoteCursor(state.cursor, state.user)
    }
  })
})
```

